explanation: The condition compared s[i][0] (the first value p of item i) to s[j][1] (the second value c of item j). That was incorrect: the intent is to compare the p values of the two items. I fixed the single line by replacing s[j][1] with s[j][0], so the code now correctly checks p_i >= p_j.
fixed_code:
n,m=map(int,input().split())
s=[]
for i in range(n):
  p,c,*f=map(int,input().split())
  s.append([p,c,f])
for i in range(n):
  for j in range(n):
    if i!=j and s[i][0]>=s[j][0] and set(s[j][2])>=set(s[i][2]) \
            and (s[i][0]>s[j][0] or set(s[j][2])-set(s[i][2])):
      print("Yes")
      exit()
print("No")
